Middle English from Old French ''[[plaisir]]'' (to please), from Latin ''[[placere]]'' (to please, to be agreeable to).

===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /pliːz/

===Verb===
'''to please'''  ([[pleases]], [[pleasing]], [[pleased]])
#''(transitive)'' To make [[happy]] or satisfy; to give [[pleasure]].



